178
00:08:44,039 --> 00:08:44,679
I'm an expert now.

179
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:46,320
Quite the professional.

180
00:08:48,399 --> 00:08:49,200
Look at the state you're in,

181
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,559
and you're still worried about that dirt?

182
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,000
It's not dirt.

183
00:08:52,559 --> 00:08:53,960
It's slightly acidic humus soil.

184
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,039
The microbial content is just right.

185
00:08:55,399 --> 00:08:56,840
With this, under-forest planting can-

186
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:57,639
Okay, okay, okay.

187
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,720
The whole village's hope, I get it.

188
00:09:00,399 --> 00:09:01,399
Glad you know.

189
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:03,919
No, really,

190
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,120
I'm just curious.

191
00:09:06,039 --> 00:09:07,200
Is your brain wired

192
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,159
differently from everyone else's?

193
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:10,440
You're banged up like this,

194
00:09:10,639 --> 00:09:11,679
and you're still thinking about that?

195
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:15,559
What else?

196
00:09:15,919 --> 00:09:16,840
Wait for you to stew up another pot?

197
00:09:17,559 --> 00:09:18,879
Can we drop that subject?

198
00:09:18,919 --> 00:09:20,360
No. Eighteen thousand.

199
00:09:20,919 --> 00:09:22,440
I remember every cent of that eighteen thousand.

200
00:09:22,519 --> 00:09:23,519
The whole village remembers.

201
00:09:24,279 --> 00:09:25,159
Good that you remember.

202
00:09:30,159 --> 00:09:31,279
Come on, hop on.

203
00:09:32,879 --> 00:09:34,120
No need, I can manage.

204
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,360
Manage, my foot.

205
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:36,799
You couldn't even stand up just now.

206
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:39,600
That's because I wasn't positioned right, I-

207
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,559
Dr. Medo,

208
00:09:40,559 --> 00:09:41,879
these mountains are dangerous.

209
00:09:42,399 --> 00:09:43,559
Either I carry you down,

210
00:09:43,759 --> 00:09:44,639
or tomorrow morning

211
00:09:44,799 --> 00:09:45,720
I come collect your bones.

212
00:09:51,919 --> 00:09:52,240
Come on.

213
00:09:58,440 --> 00:09:59,200
Hold on to me.

214
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:03,919
Your precious dirt.

215
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:11,799
Give me the box.

216
00:10:13,919 --> 00:10:14,720
And this one too.

217
00:10:19,159 --> 00:10:20,240
Just like when you were little.

218
00:10:20,759 --> 00:10:22,399
You look skinny, but you're pretty heavy.

219
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:25,120
That's because of all my equipment.

220
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:26,639
Equipment, equipment.

221
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:28,600
Equipment.

222
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:35,720
Am I really that heavy?

223
00:10:37,559 --> 00:10:38,879
Just kidding. You're not.

224
00:10:39,879 --> 00:10:41,320
That's more like it.

225
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,320
See, I can even run.

226
00:10:45,879 --> 00:10:47,039
How did you get here so fast?

227
00:10:47,679 --> 00:10:48,679
I ran here.

228
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,080
It's a few miles, and it only took me twenty minutes.

229
00:10:54,679 --> 00:10:56,120
I didn't even finish mixing the cement

230
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:56,799
at Ajia Drolma's place.

231
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,240
You were helping out,

232
00:11:01,519 --> 00:11:02,919
and didn't even notice your clothes getting dirty.

233
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:04,919
Doesn't matter.

234
00:11:05,159 --> 00:11:06,039
As long as you're okay.

235
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,279
Well, that's acceptable.

236
00:11:08,919 --> 00:11:10,360
What do you mean "acceptable"?

237
00:11:12,639 --> 00:11:14,600
It means, I get it.

238
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,200
Medo,

239
00:11:21,879 --> 00:11:23,279
